I"N<p><b>Ingredients</b></p>
<ul>
<li>1 Tsp Cumin</li>
<li>2 Tsp Salt</li>
<li>1 Tsp Paprika</li>
<li>1 Tsp Turmeric</li>
<li>1 Tsp Garam Masala</li>
<li>20g Cilantro (chopped)</li>
<li>20g Chives (chopped)</li>
<li>25g Ginger (chopped)</li>
<li>1 Green Chili (chopped)</li>
<li>400ml Chopped Tomatoes (Canned)</li>
<li>400ml Sieved Tomatoes (Canned)</li>
<li>400ml Coconut Milk</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Instructions</b></p>
<ol>
<li>Add oil, cumin and salt (1 Tsp) into the pan and fry.</li>
<li>Add Ginger, Cilantro, Green Chili, Paprika and Turmeric.</li>
<li>Add salt (1 Tsp Salt), chopped and sieved Tomatoes as well as the Coconut Milk. Cook for about 10 minutes until the soup has thickened.</li>
<li>Switch off the fire and add Chives and Garam Masala.</li>
</ol>

<p>Adapted from: <a href="https://minimalistbaker.com/easy-chana-masala/"></a></p>
